60|$|She had morphia every night, and {{her heart}} got fitful. Annie slept beside her. Paul would go in in the early morning, when his sister got up. His mother was wasted and almost ashen {{in the morning with}} the morphia. Darker and darker grew her eyes, all pupil, with the torture. In the mornings the weariness and ache were <b>too</b> <b>much</b> <b>to</b> <b>bear.</b> Yet she could not--would not--weep, or even {{complain}} much.|$|E
